cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on the problem of set-to-set recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a novel network architecture that learns the quality of each sample in a set, which involves machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also conducts experiments on face verification and person re-identification, which are subfields of multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a mechanism for simplifying the distribution that the network needs to fit, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of the proposed mechanism, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR).
